<li id="cite_note-BOETTKE-14">^ <a href="#cite_ref-BOETTKE_14-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-BOETTKE_14-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="http://www.the-dissident.com/Boettke_CR.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.the-dissident.com/Boettke_CR.pdf" rel="nofollow">BOETTKE, Peter J. <i>What Went Wrong with Economics?</i>, Critical Review Vol. 11, No. 1, P. 35. p. 58</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-SAPPINGTON-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-SAPPINGTON_15-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://elsa.berkeley.edu/~yqian/econ260b/Sappington%20Privatization.pdf" class="external text" title="http://elsa.berkeley.edu/~yqian/econ260b/Sappington%20Privatization.pdf" rel="nofollow">SAPPINGTON, David E. M. e STIGLITZ, Joseph E. <i>Privatization, Information and Incentives.</i> Columbia University; National Bureau of Economic Research (NBER) June 1988; NBER Working Paper No. W2196</a></li>
